hopobject.body: It's funny goodluck a fair deal pharmacy corona new york If you can prove that you have £20,000 of guaranteed annual pension income from other sources then you can withdraw as much as you like. This is called "flexible" drawdown. However, most people will see withdrawals subject to a cap. Currently, the amount a 65-year-old can take from a £100,000 pension pot each year is £7,320, according to pension provider LV=.
